      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a name=\"platform\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>Microsoft's Data Platform"
    },
    {
      "content": "One of the first things to understand in any discussion of Azure versus on-premises SQL Server databases is that you can use it all.",
      "pos": [
        1905,
        2037
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Microsoft’s Data Platform leverages SQL Server technology and makes it available across physical on-premises machines, private cloud environments, third-party hosted private cloud environments, and public cloud.",
      "pos": [
        2038,
        2249
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This enables you to meet unique and diverse business needs through a combination of on-premises and cloud-hosted deployments, while using the same set of server products, development tools, and expertise across these environments.",
      "pos": [
        2250,
        2480
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "![][1]",
      "pos": [
        2485,
        2491
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "As seen in the diagram, each offering can be characterized by the level of administration you have over the infrastructure (on the X axis), and by the degree of cost efficiency achieved by database level consolidation and automation (on the Y axis).",
      "pos": [
        2493,
        2742
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When designing an application, four basic options are available for hosting the SQL Server part of the application:",
      "pos": [
        2744,
        2859
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "SQL Server on nonvirtualized physical machines",
      "pos": [
        2864,
        2910
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "SQL Server in on-premises virtualized machines (private cloud)",
      "pos": [
        2914,
        2976
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "SQL Server in Azure Virtual Machine (public cloud)",
      "pos": [
        2979,
        3029
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Azure SQL Database (public cloud)",
      "pos": [
        3032,
        3065
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In the following sections, we will learn about the last two: Azure SQL Database and SQL Server in Azure VMs.",
      "pos": [
        3067,
        3175
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In addition, we will explore common business motivators for determining which option works best for your application.",
