      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a name=\"close\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>A Closer Look at Azure SQL Database and SQL Server in Azure VM"
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Microsoft Azure SQL Database (Azure SQL Database)<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> is a relational database-as-a-service, which falls into the industry category <bpt id=\"p2\">*</bpt>Platform as a Service (PaaS)<ept id=\"p2\">*</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        3381,
        3544
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Azure SQL Database is built on standardized hardware and software that is owned, hosted, and maintained by Microsoft.",
      "pos": [
        3545,
        3662
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "With SQL Database, you can develop directly on the service using built-in features and functionality.",
      "pos": [
        3663,
        3764
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When using SQL Database, you pay-as-you-go with options to scale up or out for greater power.",
      "pos": [
        3765,
        3858
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>SQL Server in Azure Virtual Machine (VM)<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> falls into the industry category <bpt id=\"p2\">*</bpt>Infrastructure as a Service (IaaS)<ept id=\"p2\">*</ept> and allows you to run SQL Server inside a virtual machine in the cloud.",
      "pos": [
        3860,
        4046
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Similar to Azure SQL Database, it is built on standardized hardware that is owned, hosted, and maintained by Microsoft.",
      "pos": [
        4047,
        4166
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When using SQL Server in a VM, you can either bring your own SQL Server license to Azure or use one of the preconfigured SQL Server images in the Azure portal.",
      "pos": [
        4167,
        4326
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In general, these two SQL options are optimized for different purposes:",
      "pos": [
        4328,
        4399
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Azure SQL Database<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> is optimized to reduce overall costs to the minimum for provisioning and managing many databases.",
      "pos": [
        4403,
        4523
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It minimizes ongoing administration costs because you do not have to manage any virtual machines, operating system or database software including upgrades, high availability, and backups.",
      "pos": [
        4524,
        4711
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In general, SQL Database can dramatically increase the number of databases managed by a single IT or development resource.",
      "pos": [
        4712,
        4834
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>SQL Server running in Azure VM<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> is optimized for extending existing on-premises SQL Server applications to Azure in a hybrid scenario or deploying an existing application to Azure in a migration scenario or dev/test scenario.",
      "pos": [
        4837,
        5065
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "An example of the hybrid scenario is keeping secondary database replicas in Azure via <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Azure Virtual Network<ept id=\"p1\">](../virtual-network/virtual-networks-overview.md)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        5066,
        5225
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "With SQL Server in Azure VMs, you have the full administrative rights over a dedicated SQL Server instance and a cloud-based VM.",
      "pos": [
        5226,
        5354
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It is a perfect choice when an organization already has IT resources available to maintain the virtual machines.",
      "pos": [
        5355,
        5467
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "With SQL Server in VM, you can build a highly customized system to address your application’s specific performance and availability requirements.",
      "pos": [
        5468,
        5613
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The following table summarizes the main characteristics of Azure SQL Database and SQL Server in Azure VM:",
      "pos": [
