    {
      "pos": [
        10623,
        10725
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a name=\"business\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>Business motivations when choosing Azure SQL Database or SQL Server in Azure VM"
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        10730,
        10753
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a name=\"cost\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>Cost"
    },
    {
      "content": "Whether you’re a startup that is strapped for cash, or a team in an established company that operates under tight budget constraints, limited funding is often the primary driver when deciding how to host your databases.",
      "pos": [
        10755,
        10974
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In this section, we’ll first learn about the billing and licensing basics in Azure with regards to these two relational database options: Azure SQL Database and SQL Server in Azure VM.",
      "pos": [
        10975,
        11159
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Then, we’ll see how we should calculate the total application cost.",
      "pos": [
        11160,
        11227
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        11233,
        11283
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a name=\"billing\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>Billing and licensing basics"
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        11285,
        11434
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Azure SQL Database<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> is sold to customers as a service not with a license whereas SQL Server in Azure VM requires traditional SQL Server licensing."
    },
    {
      "content": "Currently, <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Azure SQL Database<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> is available in several service tiers.",
      "pos": [
        11437,
        11509
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For Basic, Standard, and Premium service tiers, you are billed hourly at a fixed rate based on the service tier and performance level you choose.",
      "pos": [
        11510,
        11655
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The Basic, Standard, and Premium service tiers are designed to deliver predictable performance with multiple performance levels to match your application’s peak requirements.",
      "pos": [
        11656,
        11830
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can change between service tiers and performance levels to match your application’s varied throughput needs.",
      "pos": [
        11831,
        11943
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For the latest information on the current supported service tiers, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Azure SQL Database Service Tiers (Editions)<ept id=\"p1\">](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/azure/dn741340.aspx)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        11944,
        12116
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "With <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Azure SQL Database<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, the database software is automatically configured, patched, and upgraded by Microsoft Azure in data centers all over the world.",
      "pos": [
        12118,
        12274
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Therefore, you gain reduced administration costs.",
      "pos": [
        12275,
        12324
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In addition, its <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>built-in backup<ept id=\"p1\">](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/azure/jj650016.aspx)</ept> capabilities help you achieve significant cost savings, especially, when you have large number of databases.",
      "pos": [
        12325,
        12523
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When using Azure SQL Database, you are not billed for individual queries running against Azure SQL Database or incoming internet traffic.",
      "pos": [
        12524,
        12661
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You are billed for <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>outgoing internet traffic<ept id=\"p1\">](http://azure.microsoft.com/pricing/details/data-transfers/)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        12662,
        12769
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If your database has high transactional volume and need to support many concurrent users, we recommend that you use Premium rather than Basic or Standard service tiers.",
      "pos": [
        12770,
        12938
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "With <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>SQL Server in Azure VM<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, you utilize traditional SQL Server licensing.",
      "pos": [
        12941,
        13019
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can either use the platform-provided SQL Server image or bring your SQL Server license to Azure.",
      "pos": [
        13020,
        13120
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When using the SQL Server platform provided images, the cost depends on the VM size as well as the version of SQL Server you choose.",
      "pos": [
        13121,
        13253
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Basically, you pay per minute licensing cost of SQL Server, the per-minute licensing of Windows Server, and the Azure storage cost.",
      "pos": [
        13254,
        13385
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The per-minute billing option allows you to use SQL Server for as long as you need it without buying full SQL Server license.",
      "pos": [
        13386,
        13511
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If you bring your own SQL Server license to Azure, you are charged for Azure compute and storage costs only.",
      "pos": [
        13512,
        13620
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For more information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>License Mobility through Software Assurance on Azure<ept id=\"p1\">](http://azure.microsoft.com/pricing/license-mobility/)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        13621,
        13756
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        13762,
        13822
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a name=\"appcost\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>Calculating the total application cost"
    },
    {
      "content": "When you start using a cloud platform, the cost of running your application mainly includes the development and administration costs; and also the service costs that the public cloud platform requires.",
      "pos": [
        13824,
        14025
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Here is the detailed cost calculation for your application running in Azure SQL Database and SQL Server in Azure VM:",
      "pos": [
        14027,
        14143
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When using Azure SQL Database:",
      "pos": [
        14147,
        14177
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Total cost of application = Highly minimized administration costs + software development costs + Azure SQL Database service costs",
      "pos": [
        14182,
        14311
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When using SQL Server in Azure VM:",
      "pos": [
        14316,
        14350
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Total cost of application = Minimized software development/modification costs + administration costs +  SQL Server &amp; Windows Server licensing costs + Azure Storage costs",
      "pos": [
        14355,
        14524
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Important note:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> Currently, Azure SQL Database does not support all the features of SQL Server.",
      "pos": [
        14528,
        14626
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For a detailed comparison information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Azure SQL Database Guidelines and Limitations<ept id=\"p1\">](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/azure/ff394102.aspx)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        14627,
        14773
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Be aware of this when you want to move an existing database to Azure SQL Database as you might need some additional budget on database redesign.",
      "pos": [
        14774,
        14918
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Azure SQL Database is Microsoft’s platform as-a-service offering.",
      "pos": [
        14919,
        14984
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When you migrate an existing on-premises SQL Server application to Azure SQL Database, we recommend that you update the application to take all advantages of the platform-as-a-service offering.",
      "pos": [
        14985,
        15178
      ]
    },
    {
